name: Modern Silver Lake hillside retreat
description: Perfect for couples, solo adventurers and business travelers, our newly-remodeled guesthouse (with private entrance and patio) is a short stroll to Silver Lake’s famed Sunset Junction, home to restaurants, cafes and much more. Our Farmers Market pops up twice weekly in Sunset Triangle, which also hosts free outdoor movies over summer. So grab your seasonal market produce, freshly roasted artisanal coffee beans, whip up deliciousness back in our kitchen and enjoy it all al fresco Cali style.
neighborhood_overview:
Voted "Best Neighborhood in the USA" by Forbes Magazine, Silver Lake is one of the most famed neighborhoods in Los Angeles. Dozens of beloved (and award-winning) restaurants, cafes and bars are home to cuisines from around the world including Mh Zh, Pine & Crane, Cliffs Edge, Trois Famillia, Night + Market Song, Sawyer and Kettle Black. Coffee here is serious business, with hot shots including Intelligentsia, Alfred, La Colombe, Caffe Vita and even a barista training school at Counter Culture Coffee.
And of course there's serious shopping chops, from international brand showrooms to artisanal boutiques.

name: Central and Convenient—Next to the Hollywood Bowl!
description:
Enjoy a stylish experience in the heart of Mediterranean Whitley Heights, where Hollywood began. This centrally-located 1bdrm/2ba duplex unit is a 5 minute walk to the Hollywood Bowl, 5 mins from Universal Studios, a 15 min drive to/from Burbank Airport, 10 mins to Melrose Ave…and just a 10-15 minute walk to The Walk of Fame, the Chinese Theater, the El Capitan, the Wax Museum, Ripley’s Believe it or Not, and dozens of fabulous restaurants!

1-Car locked garage provided, more available.
neighborhood_overview:
This is where Hollywood began! Come stay in the famed Whitley Heights neighborhood, built in the 1920’s and 1930’s, where Charlie Chaplin, Bette Davis, WC Fields, Boris Karloff, and dozens of others once lived! Plenty of current celebrities reside here now as well.

Walk to dozens of nearby destinations like the Walk of Fame and Chinese Theater. Dine at Hollywood’s oldest (and newest) restaurants nearby. Stroll (or jog) the Hollywood Hills from just outside your front door.

Just a 5-minute drive to Universal Studios, Yamashiro Restaurant (the best view in LA), or the Magic Castle. In 10-minutes be on Melrose Ave, 15-minutes to Downtown LA, and 20-mins to Santa Monica or Venice.
host_about:
Our family loves to travel and do so as frequently as time and finances afford us. Most recently we’ve been to Costa Rica and loved it! We have four kids and two adorable pugs! 

As our only rental property, we’ve done our best to make this special destination as homey and comfortable for our guests as possible. If we’ve missed something, please ask and we’ll do our best to accommodate your needs. 

We manage from onsite.

Si habla espanol.

description:
This room is the guest room within our family's living area. If we are not using it for personal guests, we can make it available to returning guests or people referred by returning guests, etc.

The room includes a King bed, a desk, a dresser, etc.

You will have access to an adjacent full bath, which may be shared with our family, although our family will use our other family bath as much as possible.

host_about:
As an entertainer, I see good entertainment as merely an extension of great hospitality. I currently play trumpet for Princess Cruises and Disneyland Parks, but am also working on a magic act. I've spent the last 3 years travelling around the Mediterranean, Alaska, Japan, Mexico, and the Caribbean, Barcelona being my favorite port so far. After getting to travel, I now have a new appreciation for Los Angeles and the diversity of cultures and experiences to be found here. I now strive to take advantage of the city more whenever I'm home. 

I love eating out with friends, no matter how cheap or fancy the food is. My favorite restaurant is Souplantation, the best all-you-can-eat salad bar! I mostly listen to either classical or jazz music - right now, I'm loving everything by Ravel. I'm also really interested in small microapartments and the whole tiny house movement.

host_about:
I'm a native Angelino, living in Downtown LA for almost 9 years now and have been hosting on AirBnb for over 7 years. I work in the design + hospitality space and love to host great people from all over the world. 

I'm a foodie and love finding new places to eat or drink at. I love fashion and interior design and can suggest great boutiques to shop at, or hidden hole in the wall restaurants for amazing food. I love listening to music such as hip hop, alternative, indie and electronic. Wes Anderson, and Stanley Kubrick are two of my favorite directors.

Other things to note about me as a host: I pride myself in a very clean place, I have OCD about cleanliness. All decor details in each of my apartments are all designed by me. My style is very minimalistic without any hassle.  I'm always available for contact through the airbnb app. Having me as a host will ensure you a great stay in this amazing city.

name: MermaidsCoveLA- A hidden oasis in Los Angeles
description:
Ahoy Mateys,

Welcome to MermaidsCoveLA- A hidden oasis nestled in a quiet, urban, working class neighborhood that's central to everything Los Angeles. Come with your best pirate hat or mermaid tail and frolic amongst the rocks while you bounce from the spa to the pool. When you're done lounging around, retreat into the beautiful spanish-style home with vaulted ceilings and tons of room for everyone. Rumor has it, pirates even hid treasure amongst the property. Please, no locals.
neighborhood_overview: We are located in an quiet, urban, working class neighborhood. neighborhood_overview:
Silver Lake has comfortably maintained its position as the Eastside’s trendiest neighborhood thanks to a wealth of boutique shops and an ever-growing dining scene that makes room for both chic outdoor patios to an old-school tiki bar.

Most of the best things to do in Silver Lake are situated along Sunset Boulevard, with Sunset Junction (where the street splits with Santa Monica Boulevard) being the closest thing the neighborhood has to a walkable center. But you’ll find plenty to do elsewhere, whether on a charming stretch of Silver Lake Boulevard or tucked among the scenic hills and namesake reservoir.

While you won’t find any major museums or landmark attractions, that doesn’t mean there’s a shortage of eclectic culture. Catch a show at the Satellite, go shopping along Sunset Junction, take a stair hike between hillside houses or roll out a blanket in front of the Silver Lake Reservoir—there are plenty of worthwhile things to do in Silver Lake.

Stock

Our goal is to provide the convenience of home away from home. The home you stay at will be the cozy and likable. Eat in or eat out you will enjoy knowing that your each meal is to your liking. name: Tranquil Oasis with Historic Charm
description: Discover tranquility in our light-filled guesthouse, nestled in a charming, historic neighborhood. With its central location, perfect to explore the city's renowned attractions. Enjoy the peaceful ambiance, featuring a comfortable Queen bed, 65" 4K TV, and permit parking. Our commitment to cleanliness is ensured by dedicated professional housekeepers. neighborhood_overview:
Carthay Circle is a historic neighborhood in the heart of Los Angeles known for its architecture, including Spanish Colonial and Tudor Revival homes. It's named after the iconic Carthay Circle Theatre, which hosted significant film premieres in the 20th century. The area is characterized by its tranquility, tree-lined streets, and close-knit community.

Adjacent is Miracle Mile a bustling urban hub, famous for the "Museum Row". It houses the Los Angeles County Museum of Art (LACMA), the Petersen Automotive Museum, and the La Brea Tar Pits, among others. Lined with art deco buildings, it's a vibrant area with a rich selection of dining and shopping options.
